SIMPLE: undertaker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undertaker
<hw>Un`der*tak"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who undertakes; one who engages in any project or business.</def>
<rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who stipulates or covenants to perform any work
for another; a contractor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To sign deputations for <qex>undertakes</qex> to furnish their
proportions of saltpeter.</q> <rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In come some other <qex>undertakes</qex>, and promise us the same
or greater wonders.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Specifically, one who takes the charge and
management of funerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undertaking</ent>⟦br⟧
